{"timestamp":"2026-02-24T10:29:25.618Z","ip":"::1","question":"payment fail","answer":"Payment failure has occurred. According to our knowledge base, when a payment failure occurs, the order is considered failed.\n\n**Action Required:** \n1. Notify the user about the payment failure.\n2. Cancel the order.\n3. Inform the user that they need to retry the payment or contact customer support for assistance.\n\n**Note:** Payment failure can be due to various reasons such as invalid payment details, declined credit card, or network issues.","durationMs":1311}
{"timestamp":"2026-02-24T10:35:55.017Z","ip":"::1","question":"What happens when an order is created?","answer":"According to the Order Creation process, here's what happens when an order is created:\n\n1. The user places an order.\n2. The order service validates the request.\n3. An inventory check is performed.\n4. Payment processing occurs.\n5. The order is confirmed.\n\nIf any of these steps fail, the order may be rejected or failed. Specifically:\n\n* If payment fails, the order is failed.\n* If inventory is unavailable, the order is rejected.","durationMs":1212}
